-- RBS Hires John Briggs as Senior Vice President, U.S. Treasury Strategist
-- Cordell Eddings
-- 2010-07-07T16:14:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/rbs-hires-john-briggs-as-senior-vice-president-u-s-treasury-strategist.html

          
          
             Royal Bank of Scotland Plc, one of
the 18 primary dealers that trade directly with the Federal
Reserve, has hired  John Briggs  as an analyst.  
 Briggs, 35, will serve as senior vice president and U.S.
Treasury strategist in RBS’s Global Banking & Markets division,
according to  Michael Geller , a spokesman for RBS in Stamford,
Connecticut. He will report to  William O’Donnell , head of U.S.
Treasury trading in Stamford.  Aaron Kohli  left the firm in April
to work for Nomura Holdings Inc., another primary dealer.  
 Previously, Briggs was a proprietary trader at BWT
Professional Trading and a senior portfolio manager at Prologue
Capital. Before that, he worked at Capra Asset Management for 11
years in a variety of posts, including head trader.  
 “John brings a top-notch macro outlook, experience and in-
depth analytical skills,” O’Donnell said.  
